President Biden met with President Ramaphosa of South Africa to discuss deepening the relationship between the two countries, addressing mutual concerns, and tackling regional and global challenges. They discussed progress on trade, investment, climate, and energy. President Biden announced the creation of a South Africa-U.S. Investment Advisory Task Force and a $45 million investment towards the Just Energy Transition Partnership. They also committed to addressing urgent challenges such as the Russia-Ukraine conflict and its impact on food security in Africa. The meeting emphasized the importance of the longstanding partnership between the two countries and South Africa's influential role in global affairs.